MS NID 16/17

Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Sans Arabic SemiCondensed Light' ≠ 'Noto Sans Arabic SemCond Light' (NID 1).

Noto Sans Arabic SemCond Med Regular (NotoSansArabic-SemiCondensedMedium.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansArabic-SemiCondensedMedium', Everything looks good.

Noto Sans Arabic SemCond Med Regular (NotoSansArabic-SemiCondensedMedium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Sans Arabic SemiCondensed Medium' ≠ 'Noto Sans Arabic SemCond Med' (NID 1).

Pass
